				\begin{document}$${\mathrm{Solidity}} = \frac{A}{{CA}}$$\end{document}Solidity=ACAWhere A is the area of the cell, ma is the major axis, and CA is the convex area, namely the area of the convex hull of the region. The convex hull of a region is the smallest region that satisfies two conditions: (a) it is convex (b) it contains the original region.

